<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Britons made the most of the final evening of the three-day weekend yesterday with nights out across the country. </p>

<p>Young men and women went out for a night on the tiles on the final August weekend, with some even sporting patterned face masks. </p>

<p>One hen do was pictured heading out in Leeds, with the bride-to-be donning a sash and veil, while one of her friends clung to a novelty inflatable sheep.   </p>

<p>Many of Britain's young people were enjoying time off through social outings with their friends - with a handful of those no doubt facing sore heads as they start work this morning. </p>

